        <dc:title>DeepTest: automated testing of deep-neural-network-driven autonomous cars</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>Recent advances in Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) have led to the development of DNN-driven autonomous cars that, using sensors like camera, LiDAR, etc., can drive without any human intervention. Most major manufacturers including Tesla, GM, Ford, BMW, and Waymo/Google are working on building and testing different types of autonomous vehicles. The lawmakers of several US states including California, Texas, and New York have passed new legislation to fast-track the process of testing and deployment of autonomous vehicles on their roads.</dcterms:abstract>
        <dc:date>2018-05-27</dc:date>
        <dc:identifier>
            <dcterms:URI>
                <rdf:value>https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.1145/3180155.3180220</rdf:value>
            </dcterms:URI>
        </dc:identifier>
